save me is a 2007 film directed by robert cary about mark ( chad allen ) , a drug-addicted homosexual man who is admitted into an &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; program run by gayle ( judith light ) and her husband ted ( stephen lang ) . the film premiered at the 2007 sundance film festival and was later picked up for distribution by independent studio first run features . in september 2008 the film began its limited theatrical release in select markets in the united states . the film screened at over 6 film festivals and has drawn positive reviews from entertainment weekly , variety , time out london and several other publications .